Text: Being the first week of producing work, it has been about getting our ducks in a row.

Seeing as our project is quite large and involves a lot of moving parts, being the different entities the trust is responsible for needs to be updated, planning the agile process is essential to the success of our project and will ensure we focus on the key problem the trust is facing regarding IT.
In order to achieve our understanding of the clients needs, we began the week with interviewing Sophie, who is responsible for marketing within the OPT.
She was able to provide us with information pertaining to the problems they are facing with their current website design.
From there, we built a poster which recognized our client needs and elaborated on how we plan to accomplish and deliver on the final result week after week.
After the poster was presented, we received the feedback that our plan to accomplish such a large project was likely not feasible.
We decided to drill down our focus more which involved developing 4 key user stories over the weekend of which we researched and clearly understand the users needs.

Going into the next week, we plan to finish our research and begin our agile process plan by Wednesday, so come Friday we can have our insights from our user stories and research integrated into our first LO-FI mock ups to our client.

I am foreseeing it being a challenge to create regular meeting times with our client as she is extremely busy, this can be overcome if our team is flexible about meetings with her and schedule them to be short.
Our new plan is to design and develop the user experience for site visitors and focus on the function of the trust receiving bookings and making sales conversions.

Improvement of the user experience/customer journey pertaining to identifying the key services which attract tourists to payment is essential seeing as 80% of OPT's business was dependent on overseas tourists who no longer are visiting New Zealand with COVID restrictions.
Our plan is to facilitate OPT's pivot through helping them also attract local tourists through the re designing of their website.
